cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for 3D hand pose estimation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of geometric constraints and keypoint-based methods, which are relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses ConvNet models for learning, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed framework on benchmark datasets, which is relevant to graphics (cs.GR).
